                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/2308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 19, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Your 87, April 18, 6 p.m. was laid before the President before he left
                    Washington for Warm Springs last evening.</p>
                <p>We are giving the closest attention to the situation and we are anxious to be
                    helpful to the utmost of our ability. We would therefore appreciate being kept
                    closely informed of any developments which may come to your attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
